t: The*p Lord*s said unto my Lord, Sit thou at my right hand, until I make thine enemies thy footstool.
The*p Lord*s shall send the rod of thy strength out of Zion: rule thou in the midst of thine enemies.
Thy*p people shall be willing in the day of thy power, in the beauties of holiness from the womb of the morning: thou hast the dew of thy youth.
The*p Lord*s hath sworn, and will not repent, Thou art a priest for ever after the order of Melchizedek.
The*p Lord at thy right hand shall strike through kings in the day of his wrath.
He*p shall judge among the heathen, he shall fill the places with the dead bodies; he shall wound the heads over many countries.
He*p shall drink of the brook in the way: therefore shall he lift up the head.
